**NEWS**

Well hello @everyone - I hope you're having a purrrrrfect evening, morning or 'ing to your day. 

After working with the team, we've settled on a roadmap for the next 9 or so months. This is now recorded on our website accordingly: https://www.mewccrypto.com/roadmap

As part of this roadmap, we want to improve the tech we have to support our goals of tokenising adoption and tokenising pedigree papers.

We're also keen to ensure that the tech we build into the chain makes it attractive to other businesses.

Our dev will be beginning work on these this week. 🥳 

With this in mind, we can safely say:
* Several shelter organisations have been approached about longer term partnerships. One has provided provisional agreement to our offer and is now seeking their boards approval to proceed. A second is confirming more details from us and will advise soon. 
* We have a new **EXCHANGE** coming on Wednesday and that will be announced once it is live. 
* We are making progress on WhatToMine - please keep (nicely) reminding our friends over there that this project is not going away and indeed will be a feature of mining for years to come. 🙂 
* We have got a business opportunity that is progressing for a new start up company whereby they will use our blockchain for their technology. I won't say more than this, but it shows that our chain is more than just philanthropically minded but is useful for business too. 

If you have any Q's about the above, please just @ me in #🐈cat-chat and I'll be happy to answer. 

MEOW! 😻

**NEWS**

We now have a bot here that let's you achieve levels by being active on the discord. We're still thinking of rewards that you can get for achieving a high level, but the time we're thinking about it, you can already increase your levels! 🙂  When you rank up, you'll get notified in the #deleted-channel channel. You can use the same channel with the /rank command to check your current level 🙂

Happy leveling!

*EDIT*: I was in contact with the support of the bot - it seems, that because of some changes in discord, the /rank command doesn't work for everybody. However, you are still ranking in the background (and will see your upranks, when the bot is telling you), you just can't check it, until the problem is resolved.

**NEWS**

Hi @everyone - happy Fri-YAY! 🥳  

To keep you abreast, there's a few cool things going on behind the scenes that we wanted to keep you informed of:

1. We've been in discussions with https://www.petrescue.com.au/ and things are progressing nicely. Pet Rescue are Australia's largest facilitator of animal adoption and partner with the RSPCA to rehome animals safely. Our engagements have been positive and they're currently working through the legalities of the arrangement (corporates do take time - they have to remain compliant) but I'm optimistic that they will be able to take us on as a partner for ongoing donations. 

2. Additionally, Pet Rescue are very interested in working with us for Pet Adoption. My next meeting will be with their tech team to go through what our blockchain technology can achieve for them and how it could be easily implemented. Stay tuned on this!

3. @α | crypticwizardry.com  is working on two new wallets; an Android and a Web GUI wallet. These will both be available shortly and hopefully alleviate some of the challenges you face with Core wallet. 
 
4. We're looking to release an arcade game! @Neurofluxation  is currently crafting a well loved game using a Meowcoin skin that we're sure you'll all love. You know what else you'll love? After 14 days, the highest score will receive 20,000 $MEWC as a prize. 

5. Finally, but not least, we're excited to announce that our NFT marketplace is currently being produced. We have already begun discussions with artists to come aboard our platform with new works in support of what we're doing. But the thing we're most keen to say is @Melchizedek has agreed to launch a limited 100 NFT series of 'Meowcoin' official icons. This will be our an 'official' NFT project endorsed run. We'll talk more about this in the future, but stay tuned - this is in production and should be completed in mid-Nov.

As a bit of a final round up, I just wanted to say that we're all doing well. The project is ahead of where it should be for something we started only in September. We're thrilled with the support and community spirit shown in here and want to keep encouraging you to engage and make this a 'home'. As the project grows, price and hash will move with it and this will reward you - the miners - for all your efforts.

Lets *#keepthefaith* and roll forward. 🙂

**NEWS**

G’day @everyone

I’ve got some great progress to keep you up to date with.

**EXCHANGES** – We’re currently in discussions with two exchanges. I won’t name names (and no, I won’t cave if you offer my chocolate… Ok I might, but, unlikely) but they’re both Top 100. Now, we aren’t guaranteed to make these exchanges (I can't stress this enough - exchanges are not simple and the price is super prohibitive) but we are working towards them. Please keep your fingers and toes (and tails) crossed on this.

What can you do to help with this? 

Respect your coin. What do I mean by this? **Don’t sell for under 0.0012c US**. I realise that is a huge ask, but it's something we need to be doing. Exchanges want to see that the coins price is respected and driven. Let's do that now because it will grow us as a project. 

*REMEMBER* - The more your coin is worth? The more your bag is worth. And at the end of the day, when we’re rocketing toward the moon and flying past Elon on his Tesla rocket and then we surpass Doge as they’re chasing their tail around Pluto, you’ll think ‘Shit yeah, this is awesome!’ 

Respect your coin. Respect the price. Don’t sell for under 0.0012c US 😊 

**MINING POOLS** – As you can see, we have just been listed on MinerPool. This is a big step forward. Mining pools give credibility and decentralisation. I believe we need to be looking at additional pools, which is why I’m working with @Mana on the following Prowl schedule. Put simply, I want **2miners**. 2miners is a fantastic pool and would significantly raise the profile of the coin. More to the point, *you* should want 2miners because more pools like them mean a stronger project and increased decentralisation. So how are we going to get it?

**Persistence. Prowls. Patience. **

Our next few weeks are going to be 2miners prowl central. Be focussed, be direct, be persistent, be polite, but **PROWL** these guys. We want them, and they will learn to want us.   

We have loads more coming. The NFT marketplace is being worked on. That’s only a few weeks away. There’s some wicked cool stuff being done on a game front – you’ll all enjoy it. We have wallets nearing completion – alphas is nearly done. 

Keep mining, keep HODLing and keep prowling 😊 We love you! #miners4miners

**UPDATE FROM FORGOTTEN ANIMALS**

Hi @everyone. Please read below from the Forgotten Animals team. A great way to see the real world impact you're having 🙂 

> Dear Andrew and the Meow Coin community,
>  
> thanks to the support of the amazing crypto community we are able to continue our work in Ukraine helping volunteers and shelters in destroyed and occupied cities and making sure thousands of animals are rescued, fed, treated, neutered and cared for.
>  
> Our main focus remains on providing free neutering services across Ukraine in cities like Kharkiv, Kiyv, Dnipro, Kherson, Mariupol and many others, which greatly alleviates the workload for volunteers, as there is simply not enough food to feed all the animals abandoned because of war. With your latest contribution we're able to neuter about 20 animals (the average cost of neutering is 25 USD), thus preventing thousands from being born to suffer and provide emergency food for animals at shelters and cared for by the brave volunteers, who stayed in Ukraine despite war to help animals in need, as many lose their owners or get abandoned.
>  
> Most charities working in Ukraine are now focusing on rescuing, feeding and relocating animals, all while unneutered animals keep adding litters to the already huge army of strays suffering and dying on the streets and making the work of volunteers, who are already stretched thin and swamped with work, even harder. We are the only organisation providing neutering in Mariupol and Kherson, cities no foreign charity would work in as it's a recently occupied Russian territory.
>  
> There are still over 100.000 people in Mariupol and thousands of animals. People and animals, who have to fault they are under occupation. It doesn't mean they don't need our help anymore.
>  
> In general, since the war began in February 2022, we sterilized over 1200 cats and dogs and counting, our campaign is currently active in 10+ cities across Ukraine and we keep adding locations as the funding and the veterinarian services availability allow us to.
>  
> See attached some pictures of the animals we've helped thanks to your support, below are their stories. We are very grateful to the crypto community for their generosity.
>  
> pic 1. Lana, the dog in the photo is a survivor of ongoing shelling in Belopolye, Sumy region of Ukraine. Lana and her pup were saved by Ukrainian soldiers after the house of Victor, their owner, was destroyed by bombing and Victor was killed. The puppy was named Mavka and got a collar with the Armed Forces of Ukraine emblem. After a few days, Mavka was killed by a shell fragment…The story of Lana is incredibly sad but has a happy ending. She was lucky to survive and found a new loving owner (on the photo) thanks our volunteers, the was spayed through our free spaying campaign, so that she never has to give birth to unwanted puppies.
>  
> pic 2,3 and 4. Oleg (on the photo with a kitten he rescued, among hundreds of other animals), is just an incredible human being. Living in Zaporizzhia, Ukraine, Oleg was staying at a make-shift tent camp in the woods where he was living with and feeding all the animals he rescued, before and during the war. The place was not fit for proper housing and treatment of dozens of animals currently under his care. Yet, despite his own precarious conditions, Oleg constantly helps the elderly and the poor residents in his aread by neutering and fostering their pets. After the war started, Oleg moved to an unfinished house abandoned by its owner, that will now be used as a shelter for his animals as a more spacious, comfortable, and warm place to accommodate and foster more rescue dogs and cats. Thanks to your donation we helped Oleg neutere and feed his residents. This Christmas we will be doing a donation drive in order to help Oleg finish building some parts ot the house in order to save even more animals affected by the war.

messages.content:
Hello @everyone

I’m conscious you’re all hungry for news, so here is some info to keep you in the loop:

* **NEW EXCHANGE** - We’ve signed on to a new exchange - yiew! 🥳 

This is a stepping stone for us. I’m not sure if you saw my interview with The Hobbyist Miner but exchanges are incredibly expensive and for some US based exchanges the cost is upwards of $30k USD. This does not include liquidity nor market making which are parts of the puzzle the want you to engage with. *(Slight aside - due to US regulations, if we do not engage with a US compliant exchange, then our US miners will not be able to sufficiently use the exchange).*

So why did we choose to go with the exchange we’ll announce shortly? A few reasons:

**A.** It was affordable for where we are now.
**B.** It will improve liquidity and trading volume which is very important for a coin to be considered by larger exchanges
**C.** It is a better trading platform for those who like to trade.
**D.** It will give us new exposure and new people who wish to buy and invest. 

With this now in play, this exchange becomes a stepping stone. It lets us continue to engage with the larger exchanges and negotiate for a place at their table which will hopefully continue to drive investment. 

At this point, I wanted to put a post here from another project you’re all familiar with; Neoxa. They’re about to spend $600k to list with a Top 10 exchange. Now, the point of me identifying this is not to pass judgment on what they’re doing but identify the real cost of listings on these real top tier exchanges. 

To be very real; we don't have that type of money to invest just yet, so these smaller exchanges as stepping stones are important for us to grow.

https://neoxa.medium.com/the-new-neoxa-november-update-f66e207d1283

* **NINE LIVES ARCADE** - Our friend @Neurofluxation is close to finalising the *Nine Lives Arcade*, which is great news 🙂 It will provide some classic arcade games skinned in Meowcoin for you to waste hours, and hours, and hours and hours on. Trust me, I already have…

We've pencilled in late next week to complete this and do some testing to ensure it all works smoothly. 

* **EMPAWRIUM** - We’ve settled on a name for our NFT Marketplace and we think you’ll agree that its quite snappy! 

Empawrium will be an art NFT marketplace that everyone can use. 

We’re hoping to gradually expand out the offerings we have on Empawrium over time. Two things we’d like to do is include merchandise (anyone want a tshirt? 😉 ) as an offering and implement a buy-swap-sell function. The latter would make it a decentralised marketplace, which would be pretty cool 🙂 

* **PURRRSE** - What is this? Why, it's @α | crypticwizardry.com 's web wallet 🙂 

The great news is that is just around the corner. We've had some source code challenges which took a while to overcome plus Alph has had end of year exams to contend with. But the the wallet is now in Beta and I've tested it. With a few more tweaks to allow sending of transactions to occur it will be done 🙂 

We're aiming to have it NFT / Asset Aware and ready for Empawriums launch so you can all have an easy, simple to use alternative to the Core wallet once it goes live. 

Thank you for your patience with this one - I know we've had some delays to it. 

* **URBAN KITTIENS** - My meeting with https://www.urbankittens.com/ went well. I’m meeting again with their centre owner next Friday and will hopefully get agreement to progress into build mode. This would, of course, see us have a full use case for Meowcoin implemented - which is exciting. 

It would also mean we have a working solution that we can take to other centres in the hope to get them to use our solution.

Please feel free to ping me in #🐈cat-chat if you have any Q's.

> Greetings!
> 
> As we reflect on the past decade of lifesaving, we want to celebrate a cat who has been at our side the entire time.
> 
> Leroy came to us in November 2012. He was shy, hesitant around people, and clearly preferred the company of his feline roommates. He thrived in the free-roam rooms but often hid when people entered.

> 
> Leroy gets to enjoy the spoils of Perry's Place thanks to you and your support. 10 years of food, litter, medical treatment, and comfort items add up, but you have always come through to help cats like Leroy live their best life.
